Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addMimCap(25.10)                                              addMimCap(25.10)

Name
       addMimCap  -  Adds Metal-Insulator-Metal (MIM) cap cell(s) into the de-
       sign

Syntax
       addMimCap

       [-help]

       -cell <cellName>

       [-orient <orientation>]

       [-prefix <prefixName>]

       [{-stepX <step_in_microns> -stepY <step_in_microns>}

       [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}]][{-area {x1 y1 x2 y2} | -loc {x y}}] [-loc {x  y}
       | -offset {x y}]

       Adds Metal-Insulator-Metal (MIM) cap cell(s) into the design. This com-
       mand is used before placing the standard cells.

Parameters
       -area x1 y1 x2 y2
              Specifies  the  area in which MIM caps are to be inserted. If no
              area is specifies, MIM caps will be  inserted  in  the  complete
              core  area.  This option must be used in conjunction with -stepX
              and -stepY and is mutually exclusive with -loc.

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the MIM cap cell.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each addMimCap parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man addMimCap.

       -loc {x y}
              Inserts MIM cap cell at the specified location.

       -offset {x y}
              Specifies  the  offset in microns from the origin, in horizontal
              and vertical directions. If the -area  parameter  is  specified,
              the  origin is (x1, y1) of the box defined by -area. If -area is
              not specified, the origin is (0,0). This option must be used  in
              conjunction  with  -stepX  and  -stepY and is mutually exclusive
              with -loc.

       -orient <orientation>
              Specifies the orientation for the inserted MIM cap cell(s).

              Default: R0

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies the prefix for the inserted MIM cap cells.

       -stepX <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the distance between MIM cap cells in  the  horizontal
              direction.  This option must be used together with -stepY and is
              mutually exclusive with -loc.

       -stepY <step_in_microns>
              Specifies the distance between MIM cap cells in the vertical di-
              rection. This option must be used together with  -stepX  and  is
              mutually exclusive with -loc.

Examples
              * The  following  command  inserts  the  MIM  cap  cells of type
                mim_cell1 to a specific area, with a custom  offset,  orienta-
                tion, and step:

                addMimCap -cell mim_cell1 -orient R0 -stepX 34.56 -stepY 34.56
                -offset { 9.317 8.336 } -area 20 20 100 100

Related Information
              * deleteMimCap

